Subject: CVE-2022-44644: Apache Linkis (incubating): The DatasourceManager
 module has a Local File Read Vulnerability 

Severity: important

Description:

In Apache Linkis <=1.3.0 when used with the MySQL Connector/J, an authenticated attacker could read arbitrary local file by connecting a rogue mysql server, By adding allowLoadLocalInfile to true in the jdbc parameter. Therefore, the parameters in the jdbc url should be blacklisted. Versions of Apache Linkis <= 1.3.0 will be affected.Â 

We recommend users upgrade the version of Linkis to version 1.3

